text.text:
We dined here on a Tuesday evening.
It was relatively busy for a weekday evening.
The restaurant isn't very big, nice and cosy in over sense, or intimate in another way to put it.
Each dish was small, and was kind of like Japanese Tapas.
We tried quite a few items on their menu, then ordered some repeats.
Pricing wasn't too bad, but it is a bar (there are 4 seats at the bar, the rest are normal tables).
Since it is a bar, everyone needs to be over 18 - no issue for me, but some people want to complain about it regardless.
I found this to be a good thing, as there were no little ones running around causing mayhem. I could sit there and appreciate the meal without distractions.
Staff were friendly, service was good, we would go again.
There was a sign on the Oscar Street entrance, but the restaurant is actually over near the Neridah Street side of the complex.

Unassuming sushi place in Chatswood. Bit of a wait but I would say it’s worthwhile.

Decent Menu range of offerings to order from. It was our first time and we went for most of the specials available! Fish was fresh and if you’ve been to Japan it’s similar in the sense that the slices of fish is nice and big with just enough rice.

Service was good and fast! As the premise is relatively small, I would advise for customers to be mindful of the wait outside if you see a line to be considerate to share the love of good sushi with others.👍😊

This is our new found sushi place for sure! Will be returning!

So excited whenever I knew there’s a new sushi place in Sydney🤭🍣‼️This place was newly opened in Chatswood and ran by Japanese! 🇯🇵 THE owner and staff are all so nice and welcoming! What’s most important is they serve quality but affordable food! 🍱🫶🏻✨

My fav was the Hokkaido don which is their signature and topped with many premium and fresh sashimi including Uni🥹💝😋🍱 and I was surprised by the portion of the lunch combination set —— it’s just $26.8 and you’re able to choose your own don and noodles, which both of them are in standard size 😱✨ I picked the eel don and cold soba —— the soba was sooo good idk how they managed to make the sauce to be perfect🍜 and they’re just so refreshing! Best choice in summer right! 💁🏼‍♀️ another highlight was the king crab which’s also a must order! 🦀 and highly recommend the salmon lover set if you’re a salmon lover like us , they came with 4 diff versions of salmon sushi and they’re so good! 🍣😋

What I ordered:
🌟Hokkaido don (premium sashimi rice Bowl) $34
🌟Lunch combination Set (Eel Don + Cold Soba) $26.8
🌟Salmon Lover Set $26
🌟Scampi Nigiri $13
Sashimi Ceviche $17.8
Tiger Roll $16
🌟Vinegar King Crab with seaweed $12.8
Hot Green Tea $4.5
Lemon Sour $9

Weekdays are the best time to come and reservations are recommended on weekends!

text.text:
Wow. Where do I even begin. I was expecting a lot at first, perhaps my expectations were too high. AND YET! Sushi Dan still did not fail to AMAZE me! A glorious endeavour into a delicious landscape of food and sushi and vegetable tempera and udon and rice. Each bite was filled to the brim, some might say, the maximum, with that delicious taste of umami. BUT WAIT, THERE'S MORE!

Alfred, Alfred, Alfred. I was served by a charming young lad, whose service was impeccable. It is truly so marvellous to see individuals in this young generation still so hardworking, preserving the tentative balance between work, food, and life. Please get him a pay raise. There is truly nobody in this world who deserves it more. Who knows what it'll fund? His dreams, his passions, perhaps?

Not only that, it was located only a small distance from the heart of Chatswood, Chatswood interchange. It is in Chatswood Mandarin Center, surrounded by a bustling hub of restaurants, and yet, only Sushi Dan caught my eye.

The price was spectacular, I paid only roughly $14.50 with a delicious vegetable tempura udon. Wow! What a deal.

Please consider going to Sushi Dan!

text.text:
We visited Dopa for dinner one evening at Chatswood Chase. The restaurant had a slightly sterile atmosphere, but as we were craving Japanese food and rice bowls (donburi), we decided to give it a try.

The menu was simple and easy to navigate, with pictures to help choose dishes that looked appetising. We opted for the beef tongue and pork don. Both dishes were flavoursome and well-prepared, but the serving sizes were on the smaller side. We wished there had been a bit more rice, as we were still feeling a little peckish after finishing our respective meals.

That said, the pricing was great, so it’s hard to complain too much. Dopa is a good option for a quick, tasty, and affordable Japanese meal, though don’t expect satisfying portions.

Hot food like donburi and bento boxes are not bad. Great for take away

text.text: One of the best japanese takeaway shops I've been to. It's seriously dine in restaurant quality, very fresh and tasty its worth the price, and just visually it's so appealing and ingredients are all high quality. For price you will be lucky to find such a high quality sushi/sashimi Bento.

text.text: We popped into Mikazuki for a weekday lunch and left completely impressed. The clam ramen is an absolute must-try—rich, briny broth with deep umami flavor and perfectly chewy noodles. Every spoonful was pure comfort. Service was quick and the staff were genuinely warm and helpful. The vibe is cozy but modern, great for a casual meal. The seating is comfortable. Easy ordering system. Prices are reasonable.

text.text:
It's very hard to give more than 3 stars, because some food was really good and some really bad... let's start... I came for lunch, and I ordered an edamame, takoyakis,gyozas, rainbow sushi,tuna cryspy taco, and salmon collar.
Edamame was sweet even when I ordered the spycy garlic option.. and was cook well. The same happens with the gyozas. The pastry was hard.
Salmon and tuna taco are really good!!! It was very tasty and a great balance.
Sushi roll i thing the rice have to be more rice vinegar,
The service was fast and the cashier was very friendly.

text.text:
Mikazuki Chatswood locates at Victoria Avenue next to one of the most busy entrances to Westfield Chatswood.
There are 2 eating floors and we are asked to go upstairs for table #19
The salmon is fresh in the poke bowls and sushi roll. It’s worthy to pay extra $3 for a set of mini salad + mini miso soup.
The edamame is also nice to mix with truffle sauce. The quality of prawn and vegetable tempura is good.
Parking is convenient at Westfield carpark.

text.text: Been here a couple times and it’s a consistently good Japanese option. The staff was kind enough to let us in just before the kitchen closed and service was prompt. Portions are decent and the menu has a wide variety of dishes. We got the sashimi sushi set today which was presented beautifully and was nice and fresh! We also got the tempura vegetables which was a generous serving but a bit oily.

displayName.text: Hanasuki Chatswood しゃぶしゃぶ

text.text: This is probably one of the nicest Japanese hotpot restaurants in Sydney. The interior design, the cleanliness, the service is all top notch. The Wagyu selection was so good everything melts in your mouth. Only reason it doesn’t get 5 stars is it is extremely expensive - 4 of us spent an easy $500 and we weren’t really full.

text.text: Wife had a pregnancy craving for hotpot, so we booked and went to Hanasuki despite it being the middle of summer. Thought it’d be too hot and a bit of a heavy meal, but was pleasantly surprised by the opposite. Excellent meal - should have never doubted considering its sister shop is “Choji Yakiniku”. Staff was extremely friendly and helpful, but service was a little slow, probably because it was such a quiet day. Aside from that, we would definitely go again. Extra points for kid meals and being super welcoming to our son.

text.text:
We went a la carte for our first time here in Shabu shabu style and chose a range of seafood and wagyu. High quality ingredients, would recommend the wagyu especially, and clean flavours. We ate in summer and it didn’t feel too hot at all. Looking at the set menu for next time as it offers good value (refillable veggies!).

Staff helped explain how long to DIY cook produce in the soup. Condiment bar on the side. They had a surprise birthday dessert too for the occasion - so thoughtful, the token was greatly appreciated and elevates the service and experience here.

Relaxing, aesthetically pleasing and spacious fit out. Had a great weeknight evening here, thank you! Will recommend and spread the word to others.

We had an exceptional time at Hanasuki. We really enjoyed the food and we had great service. We tried the seasonal Motsunabe and it was authentic and delicious! The food was fresh, good quality and well seasoned.
Can’t wait for the next time we get to come back. Highly recommend!!!

text.text:
The restaurant is very accommodating. Service was top-notch, the waitresses were all so lovely and attentive.
We ordered set menu which comes with entree, main course or shabu shabu, japanese congee and ice cream for desert. We definitely left with a full belly! The experience is wa totally worth it. I will definitely be back in the future.
